Reasoning: The paper discusses the space of possible minds and their ability to perform non-boring activities, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of "fun space" and mapping minds to it suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and potentially computer graphics (cs.CC) or social computing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper may touch on machine learning (cs.LG) as a means of understanding and predicting the preferences of different types of minds.
